# Comms copy rules

When editing files under `content/comms/`:

1. **Trigger first** — Every template maps to a `triggerId` in `docs/comms-triggers/TRIGGER_CATALOG.md`. Do not draft orphan copy.
2. **Placeholders only** — Use `{{variable}}`; never real user PII, tokens, or secrets.
3. **One edition per file** — Clear filenames (`sphere-2026-inaugural.md`, `welcome-first-login.md`).
4. **Channel sections** — Document push, inApp, email variants in the draft or metadata table.
5. **Sync rule** — Markdown edits ship in the **same PR** as `implementationModule` updates (see `content/comms/README.md`).
6. **Registry** — New `templateId` requires `src/features/comms/registry.js` entry.
7. **Commercial** — Copy under `content/comms/commercial/` only after `docs/comms-triggers/COMMERCIAL_PHASE3.md` gates; include disclosure labels.
8. **Invoke drafter skill** — Follow `.cursor/skills/comms-drafter/SKILL.md` for full workflow.
